\begin_layout Subsubsection
Spikes Detector
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The spikes detector quantifies the percentage of signal's slew rate above
 than a threshold 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "dieter-cinc"

\end_inset

.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
SD=\underset{}{max}\left\{ \dfrac{1}{N}\sum_{n=1}^{N}\left[\dfrac{d\boldsymbol{S}[n]}{dt}\geq th\right]\right\} 
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The value 
\begin_inset Formula $th$
\end_inset

 was obtained analysing the slew rate of the QRS complex in the entire mitdb.
 We calculated the maximum slew rate in a 200 ms window centred in each
 QRS complex.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In Figure 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig:SR-HIST"

\end_inset

 the histogram of the maximum slew rates of each QRS complex is shown.
 We adopted the 
\begin_inset Formula $90th$
\end_inset

 percentile of the histogram, resulting in a
\begin_inset Formula $th$
\end_inset

 value of 
\begin_inset Formula $189\,\nicefrac{mV}{sec}$
\end_inset

.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We calculate the 
\begin_inset Formula $SD$
\end_inset

 for all the recordings without flatlines and we perform the ROC curve.
 Considering a true positive error of 
\begin_inset Formula $1\%$
\end_inset

 as acceptable, we assume a condition of 
\begin_inset Formula $10\%$
\end_inset

 of spikes to classify the record as unacceptable, as is shown in Figure
 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig:SP-ROC"

\end_inset

.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection
Step Detector
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Similar to 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "chengyu-cinc"

\end_inset

, this detector tries to detect the signals which haves a lot of energy.
 For doing that, the median value is subtracted from the record and then
 it is divided in 10 sections.
 As the QRS complex have a maximum value of 
\begin_inset Formula $800\mu V$
\end_inset

, if any sample of a section is higher than 
\begin_inset Formula $1mV$
\end_inset

, then the section is considered bad quality.
 At least 3 bad quality section are needed for considerate the record as
 unacceptable.
 
